Load the U.S. clinical cases data sets.

The reported clinical cases data sets for the years 2016 - 2021 contain the same variables but do not have the same column names. Therefore, before merging these data sets, we standardized the column names and removed missing values.

Mutate new columns coding for genes and drug resistance

Mutating Data for showing resistance: add column: - NR: Not resistant to FCZ or MCF (both == “Not_Resistant”) - FCZ: Resistant to FCZ but not MCF or AMB - MCF: Resistant to MCF but not FCZ or AMB - AMB: Resistant to AMB not MCF or FCZ - MDR: Resisant to 2/3 drugs - XDR: Resistant to AMB, FCZ, and MCF (all== “Resistant”)

Want to make graph of case#’s of these to show AMR resistance increase

Mutating data for showing ERG11 and FKS1 gene presence: - ERG11: erg11!= “WT” , fks1==“WT” - FKS1: fks1 !=“WT”, erg11== “WT” - ERG11 and FKS1: erg11!= “WT”, fks1 !=“WT” _ No AMR genes: fks1==“WT”, erg11`== “WT”
